<Content>Good resort hotel We liked the Ritz in Bali. A few of the good things we liked were the staff was very nice. The pools were impressive, the views amazing and the food was very good.A few of the things we didn't like. We had some ants in our room when we got there so we called and changed rooms. The rooms were fine but seemed a bit worn, I think the tropical climate may do that. The common area and restaurants were very nice. Also, especially as an American in Bali we didn't feel especially safe outside the hotel grounds so we spent more of our time in the resort than out of it. It is not a knock on the hotel, and actually could be a plus for the hotel because there are enough restaurants, pools etc that for a short trip you don't need to leave the resort.We did go to the beach part of the resort one day and it was not great. I don't know if other hotels mhave big nice beaches but this resort is more focused on the pools and the views. 
