<Content>Incredible resort! My girlfriend and I only spent two nights here upon arriving in Bali, but what an experience! After the Ritz shuttle drove us to the hotel, we were met with leis, intoxicating fragrant towels, welcome drinks and a hot bath full of aromatic orchids. After 30 hours of travel from the States, the Ritz Bali was the perfect cure for the jetleg.Because our Deluxe Ocean View Room was unavailable, we were upgraded to a Suite (we didn't complain). The view had a nice balcony with views of the gardens and the Indian Ocean. It was a great spot to enjoy a cocktail before heading out for the night. If I had to choose one quality which stands out among the positive features of this resort, it鈥檚 definitely the grounds. The resort is a landscaping masterpiece. Colorful flowers adorn the surroundings and the three infinity pools and make for the perfect relaxing environment during the day. The breakfast buffet was delicious and the eating area is situated among various fish ponds which dot the resort. For an unforgettable experience, I highly recommend the Pesta Lobster dinner; it's a 5-course private dinner on the pier complete with your own private percussion band playing music in the background. As you watch the gorgeous sunset, you can hear the crashing of the Indian Ocean waves beneath you. For the quality of the food, the ambience and the fact that it鈥檚 at the Ritz, it is a great deal for your money. Keep in mind you must reserve ahead of time, and accommodations can be made through the website. The staff is very friendly and helpful and they treat you like royalty the entire time. We enjoyed the spa, including the Balinese massage and the Eternal Couples package. Both were excellent. 
