<Content>Good but not great Stayed at the Ritz for 4 days in April but were not too excited about it. Weather was bad - thunderstorms and constant raining (of course not the Ritz' fault). We have been to Bali many a times (4 Seasons, Melia, Sofitel, Oberoi, Club at Legian, etc) but were a little bit disappointed about the Ritz and its location.Plus: Overall architecture is very nice; main pool area beautiful and fun to hang around; drinks/food service good and staff are attentive. Salt-water pool down at the cliffs was excellent.Minus: Location - if you're used to Legian/Seminyak area with plenty of cheap but delicious restaurants and convenience stores down the road you will be disappointed. Tried some of the in-house restaurants but thought them to be way over-priced and portions very small (especially the Thai restaurant down the stairs from the lobby). Accomodation - room was OK but nothing to be excited about. Probably wouldn't stay at the Ritz again due to prices and limited location. 
