<Content>Fantastic spot with kids Had a week at the resort with our two young kids. We stayed in a garden view room on the ground floor that was the cheapest in the hotel. The room was perfect - 2 double beds and huge bathroom, with a lovely terrace.Great kids club with enthusiastic child minders. Separate kids pools with water slides. Children's menu in all the restaurants. Babysitting available at night at 拢3 an hour.We ate in all 5 restaurants - Italian, Thai, Seafood, Japanese and International. They were all fantastic, but special mention must be made of Dava. Dava is the international restaurant, and the food is Asian Fusion. The setting is stunning at the top of a cliff amongst carp ponds and flaming torches providing the lighting.Spa is the best in Asia.If you can afford it, stay in a villa. But the standard rooms are great too. 
