<Content>sun loungers were dirty and pool overcrowded I wouldn't stay there again.I returned 21th June 2005.I 've been to Bali several times and The ritz is one of the worst hotels I have stayed at, for what you pay anyway.for the same price you can stay at The Legian in Seminyak which is 10 times better.The Ritz has 2 pools, the main pool is very overcrowded and the sunbeds are disgusting. and very dirty.the grounds sorrounding dont seem too clean either.the towels are old and worn out.The staff by the pool are rude and it is very difficult to get a drink.However the villa pool is small but much better,the sunbeds are comfortable and clean, service is great and cocktails are very nice.the restaurant above the pool DAVA has great food but is not very balinese.Our room was including breakfast, the restaurant was very very crowded and food quality wasn't brilliant.tea cups weren't too clean either.The view of the ocean isn't great although we had an deluxe ocean view suite, and there is a small beach but you can't swim there at all.the room was nice but quite noisy and the hotel is miles from anywhere.And there is nothing to do at nite in the hotel and there is no entertainment.The hotel is on a cliff and there are lots of steps and you can hardly see the ocean.the aquatonic pool in the spa is great, it costs $40 for 2 hours, but you can easily stay in another hotel and visit the spa just for the aquatonic pool.be careful, do not spend more than 2 hours inside and don't wear a light coloured bikini.If you have any sense you wouldn't stay there. not worth the money at all.but if you do stay at the ritz remember to visit the C BAR and The villa pool, and DAVA restaurant.hotel staff will take you there in a little car.P.s. if you use bluebird taxis outside the hotel, they are much cheaper.Does not compare with The Ritz in other countries. AWFUL 
